    "Suppose that X ∈ St(m, r), U ∈ St(m, r A) and r A ≤ r. Let U ⊥ ∈ R m×(m-r A) be the orthogonal complement of U. Denote Φ = U ⊤ X and Ω = U ⊤ ⊥ X.",
